University of Chicago Online Consent Form for Research Participation

 

Study Title: Online News Information Study 

Researcher(s): Boaz Keysar

 

Description: We are researchers at the University of Chicago doing a research study about information about homelessness. To qualify to participate, you must be fluent in English and are currently living in the United States. Participation should take about 5 minutes to complete. Your participation is voluntary.

 

Incentives: For completing this study, you will be paid $11.44 per hour for your time.

Risks and Benefits: Participation in this study does not pose any risks to you bond that of everyday life. Benefits of this study include learning more about news information in the United States.

Confidentiality: All data collected for this study will not be linked to personally identifiable information (names, emails, addresses, etc.) and will be stored on a password protected server. De-identified information from this study may be used for future research studies or shared with other researchers for future research without your additional informed consent. If you decide to withdraw from this study, data collected up until the point of withdrawal will be destroyed. 

 

Contacts & Questions:
If you have questions or concerns about the study, you can contact the researchers at Boaz Keysar (bkbk@uchicago.edu) If you have any questions about your rights as a participant in this research, feel you have been harmed, or wish to discuss other study-related concerns with someone who is not part of the research team, you can contact the University of Chicago Social & Behavioral Sciences Institutional Review Board (IRB) Office by phone at (773) 702-2915, or by email at sbs-irb@uchicago.edu.

 

 

Consent:

Participation is voluntary. Refusal to participate or withdrawing from the research will involve no penalty or loss of benefits to which you might otherwise be entitled.

By selecting “Agree” below, you confirm that you have read the consent form, are at least 18 years old, and agree to participate in the research. Please print or save a copy of this page for your records.
